          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>Dear Sir,  <placeName>Kingston</placeName>
                                        <date>23<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> May 1853</date></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Although not acquainted either personally or<lb/>
                                        by correspondence I am induced to address you in reply
                                        to<lb/> a Letter which was handed me by <persName>Mr Isaac
                                                  Lauton</persName> dated<lb/>
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                                        <date>1 April</date>. Accordingly I wrote <persName>Mr Moses
                                                  Saifaty</persName><lb/> giving him all the
                                        satisfaction I possibly could that I was<lb/> the rightful
                                        claimant to the Book written by my Honored<lb/> Grand Father
                                                  <persName>Benjamin Dias Fernandes</persName> which
                                        was sent<lb/> you by the late <persName>Miss Grace
                                                  Aguilar</persName> from
                                                  <placeName>England</placeName> &amp; from<lb/>
                                        which you took many Extracts no doubt an Excellent<lb/> work
                                                  <persName>Mr M Saifaty</persName> called on me and
                                        looked on the<lb/> Original Letter and supposed not to be in
                                        your hand writing<lb/> and more a h<add>?</add> on me I
                                        think it in that care one more<lb/> on you &amp; taking a
                                        liberty of making use of your name<lb/> I gave <persName>Mr
                                                  Saifaty</persName> a copy of the Letter &amp; no
                                        doubt he<lb/> has written you on the subject having a number
                                        of things<lb/> to attend to &amp; to avoid
                                        <add>?</add>olescity will say no more<lb/> on</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>on the subject for the present until you are convinced that<lb/>
                                        the letter came from you or not</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">I am with the greatest Respect</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">your O Servant</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <persName role="author">David Dias Fernandes</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <sic>
                                                  <addressee>Reverend Isaac Lesser</addressee>
                                        </sic>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>P American Steamer</p>
                    </body>
